KISUMU: Maseno University students have been fined Sh2,000 each after they went on rampage over colleague&#39;s death.They will also be required to declare that they will uphold &#39;good conduct&#39; as a pre-condition for readmission.The university&rsquo;s PR Officer, Owen McOnyango said the penalty was arrived at by the varsity senate as a deterrent measure against unrests. The 12,000 students will report back Sunday and Monday, with normal school business expected to resume immediately, according to an internal memo.The students protested after one of their colleagues was killed in unclear circumstances on Monday evening. They lynched the suspected killer before turning their anger on business premises and the public, forcing the management to close it.